with transformations, i.e. with mtcars find the gear levels with the two highest average mpg and then filter for cars with those gear levels

# step 1: find the gears with max mean mpg
topgears <- mtcars |> 
  group_by(gear) |> 
  summarize(meanmpg = mean(mpg)) |> 
  slice_max(meanmpg, n = 2) |> 
  pull(gear)

topgears

# step 2: filter
mtcars |> filter(gear %in% topgears)

Cases to tables

Pairs mosaic plots, chi-squared test

xtabs() (counts –> table)

# watch out: summarise
rebates <- read_csv("https://data.ny.gov/resource/thd2-fu8y.csv")
rebate_counts <- rebates |> group_by(make, ev_type) |> 
  summarize(Freq = n())

Continuous to categorical variables

cut()

set.seed(31)
testscore <- round(runif(100, min = 70, max = 100))
df <- data.frame(testscore) |> 
  mutate(grade = cut(testscore, breaks = seq(70, 100, 10), 
                     labels = c("C", "B", "A"), right = FALSE,
                     include.lowest = TRUE))
